Defendant Tyvex Nassar Benford in court with attorney Michael Jude.  Defendant Tyvex Nassar Benford in custody.  Alyssa M. Schaller appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

As to Count 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  2 YEARS CONSECUTIVE to the sentences ordered in case #13CF4470 and case #13CF563; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEAR and 6 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 6 MONTHS.

Court finds defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration program and the WI Substance Abuse program.


As to Count 2: 
Court withheld the sentence and placed the defendant on 2 years of probation.  Court ordered probabtion to begin after the sentence in Count 1 was completed.


Court read the Witten Explanation of Determinate Sentence to the defendant.


Conditions of Extended Supervision/Probation:
-Provide a DNA sample.
-Restitution in the amount of $469.99 payable to Sharquis R.; 


Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
Restitution in the amount of $469.99 payable to Sharquis R. as mentioned prior; 
All court costs, fees, and surcharges (including DNA); 
- Court ordered that restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision/probation. DOC shall collect those sums.  

The Court objects to expungement unless and until restitution is paid in full.
